Learnings from Heat Map ¶

As it can be observed from the heatmap and scores, there are some features that are quite correlated each other (The lighter the color, the more correlated they are) Therefore, in the lights of findings below: feature selection is applied.

1) radius_mean, perimeter_mean and area_mean are correlated with each other. The Grid from the previous work also proved that Area_mean is correlated to some of them, therefore selecting Area Mean to proceed is a good idea.

2) Compactness_mean, concavity_mean and concave points_mean are also correlated with each other. , Concavity Mean is selected to proceed.

3) Another group that is correlated each other consists these features: radius_se, perimeter_se and area_se are correlated. area_se is selected

A New dataset is created with available features to work on for ML algorithm

Feautre Extraction with Principle Component Analysis¶

In [29]:
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)
#normalization
x_train_N = (x_train-x_train.mean())/(x_train.max()-x_train.min())
x_test_N = (x_test-x_test.mean())/(x_test.max()-x_test.min())

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
pca = PCA()
pca.fit(x_train_N)

plt.figure(1, figsize=(14, 13))
plt.clf()
plt.axes([.2, .2, .7, .7])
plt.plot(pca.explained_variance_ratio_, linewidth=2)
plt.axis('tight')
plt.xlabel('n_components')
plt.ylabel('explained_variance_ratio_')
